Flights resume after ash cloud chaos
Domestic flights across southern Australia have resumed today as ash from a Chilean volcano clears, but some international flights have been suspended or delayed.
Qantas and Jetstar flights to and from Sydney resumed at 2pm, Virgin Australia flights were back in the air from 3pm and Tiger Airways resumed from 4pm.
Flights into and out of Melbourne are back on schedule for Qantas, Jetstar and Virgin.
Tiger Airways' Melbourne flights have resumed, apart from two cancellations of flights to and from the Gold Coast and Hobart.